org.tms.api.io.options

Class StyledPageOptions<S extends StyledPageOptions<S>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.tms.api.io.options.IOOptions
      • org.tms.api.io.options.StyledPageOptions<S>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - the type of IOOptions in this StyledPageOptions
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    StyleableOption
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    TitledPageOptions, XlsOptions

    public abstract class StyledPageOptions<S extends StyledPageOptions<S>>
extends IOOptions
implements StyleableOption
    The base class which IOOptions that support display styling extend. Style elements that are supported include:
    • column widths,
    • row label column widths,
    • table cell value font size,
    • heading font size, and
    • font family.
    All widths and sizes are in pixels, unless otherwise noted.

    Note: StyleableOption methods only affect export operations.

    Since:
    "1.1"
    Version:
    "1.1"
    See Also:
    StyleableOption

      • withRowLabels

        public S withRowLabels()
        Returns a new IOOptions with row labels enabled. When exporting, this means that labels assigned to the Rows in the exported Table will be included in the output. When importing, this means that row labels assigned to the data in the import file will be assigned to the Rows read from the file.
        Specified by:
        withRowLabels in class IOOptions
        Returns:
        a new StyledPageOptions with row labels enabled

      • withRowLabels

        public S withRowLabels(boolean b)
        Returns a new IOOptions with row labels enabled or disabled, as per the supplied parameter b. When exporting, this means that when enabled, labels assigned to the Rows in the exported Table will be included in the output. When disabled, row labels in the exported table are ignored and are not included in the output. When importing, this means that when enabled, row labels assigned to the data in the import file will be assigned to the Rows read from the file.
        Specified by:
        withRowLabels in class IOOptions
        Parameters:
        b - true to include Row labels, false to ignore them
        Returns:
        a new StyledPageOptions with row labels enabled or disabled

      • withIgnoreEmptyRows

        public S withIgnoreEmptyRows(boolean b)
        Sets the behavior this IOOptions uses to handle empty rows. When set to true, empty rows in the source Table are ignored (not written to the output file). On import, empty rows in the source file are ignored. When set to false, empty rows are included in the exported file, in a file-format-appropriate manner. On import, empty Rows are inserted into the new Table when encountered in the imported file.
        Specified by:
        withIgnoreEmptyRows in class IOOptions
        Parameters:
        b - true to import/export empty Rows, false to ignore them
        Returns:
        a new StyledPageOptions where empty rows are or are not ignored
